originalText.text: Today was my second time there and I have no complaints. Only been there for massages and had them both with  Esmeralda, she has amazing hands, super attentive and made me feel comfortable.

originalText.text: At my second experience here, these people overcharged me by $40. I went in there not asking for prices which was my first mistake, but already calculated the services they had on their brochure. I knew something was wrong when the lady upfront skipped the option to tip. It was because she had knowingly charged me extra. The nail service was trash, the French on my toenails & fingernails was a disaster, lines were crooked. Stones were falling off my manicure, literally on day 2. I got charge $90 for a mani and pedi, when i usually get acrylics and pedi and pay around $70 somewhere else. These people are thieves. You can’t trust Dominicans, when you go into any establishment make sure to ask for prices or they will literally take advantage. I got a Brazilian, half leg and underarm wax. Only wax that was decent was the underarms. The Brazilian left me irritated for the next two days, my legs were botched because homegirl literally left patches of hair which I had to shave later on. I’m so upset that I paid for mediocre service & not only that they overcharged me. ROBBERY.

originalText.text:
I came in for a “special” facial. I usually go to my routine place for my facials, but I wanted to support local small businesses, so I came here.
I’m not one to bruise or scar easily, however, it’s been THREE weeks and my face is still scarred from the most painful extractions I’ve ever had up to this day… extractions should never hurt as much as they did and then still leave your pores in a similar condition as you came in…my esthetician seemed like she didn’t want to be there and half as*ed the facial, she was constantly on her phone for a majority of the facial. The jelly mask was cool, and the establishment itself was nice. Maybe will try again with another esthetician for a better experience.
